On the minus side, your method for presenting amended procedures was not super effective without a re-read, and similarly some parts of the description weren't entirely clear.

(Also, on a philosophical level, the huge number of ghosts in the room suggests explaining New York homelessness through an SCP, which leans towards that taking-inappropriate-credit-for-real-tragedy pitfall for me. This isn't a huge complaint from me, since it's a damn good story, just enough to be worth mentioning.)

On the plus side, the story as told through the event and interviews was deeply engrossing, appropriately nonsensical, and still mysterious enough to survive the explaining. Well done.







