26 Feb 2016 00:54






+Spoilers

-Hide


SCP-2227-A is trapped within the subway systems, just like the rest of the hobos. He's using people to his advantage, and he is well aware of this. I won't say exactly why he's doing it, but the people in the pictures he points out to (as told by George) are part of the reason.

SCP-2227-A isn't a total bad guy either. George was the first person to not see the shadow man as a brooding eldritch monster, but rather as someone who also happens to be stuck. Assuming SCP-2227-A has full control over who becomes a ghost hobo, he has perhaps even recruited people for help, rather than labor.

And maybe, just maybe, SCP-2227-A has gotten a change of heart.








